<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>CDAC CCEE Mock Test — RTOS · IoT · Device Drivers · Aptitude</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --ink:#10151c;
    --paper:#f4f2ec;
    --panel:#ffffff;
    --line:#dcd7c9;
    --navy:#16243d;
    --navy-deep:#0c1626;
    --gold:#b5862f;
    --gold-soft:#e8c97a;
    --green:#2f7d56;
    --green-soft:#e3f1e9;
    --violet:#6a4e9c;
    --violet-soft:#ece6f6;
    --red:#a23b3b;
    --muted:#6b6557;
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;}
  body{
    margin:0;
    background:var(--paper);
    color:var(--ink);
  }
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';src:local('Segoe UI');}

  /* ---------- TOP BAR ---------- */
  .topbar{
    background:var(--navy);
    color:#f4f2ec;
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:space-between;
    padding:14px 26px;
    border-bottom:3px solid var(--gold);
  }
  .brand{
    display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px;
  }
  .brand .mark{
    width:34px;height:34px;border-radius:3px;
    background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--gold-soft),var(--gold));
    display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
    font-weight:700;color:var(--navy-deep);font-size:15px;
    font-family:Georgia,serif;
  }
  .brand .title{font-size:14px;letter-spacing:.04em;line-height:1.3;}
  .brand .title b{display:block;font-size:16px;font-family:Georgia,'Times New Roman',serif;letter-spacing:.02em;}
  .topbar .meta{display:flex; gap:26px; font-size:12.5px; color:#cfd6e2;}
  .topbar .meta div b{color:#fff; display:block; font-size:13.5px; font-family:'Courier New',monospace;}

  /* ---------- LAYOUT ---------- */
  .stage{
    max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:22px 22px 60px;
  }
  .examGrid{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap:20px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px){ .examGrid{grid-template-columns:1fr;} }

  /* ---------- QUESTION PANEL ---------- */
  .qpanel{
    background:var(--panel);
    border:1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius:4px;
    overflow:hidden;
  }
  .qbar{
    display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;
    padding:13px 20px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);
    background:#fbfaf6;
  }
  .qbar .tag{
    font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase;
    padding:4px 10px; border-radius:20px; font-weight:600;
  }
  .tag-RTOS{background:#eaf1fb;color:#2a5a96;}
  .tag-IOT{background:var(--green-soft);color:var(--green);}
  .tag-EDD{background:var(--violet-soft);color:var(--violet);}
  .tag-APT{background:#fbeee0;color:#a3601a;}
  .qbar .qnum{font-family:Georgia,serif; font-size:15px; color:var(--muted);}

  .qbody{padding:26px 30px 10px;}
  .qtext{font-size:17.5px; line-height:1.55; margin:0 0 22px; font-weight:500;}
  .options{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;margin-bottom:8px;}
  .opt{
    display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;
    border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px;
    padding:12px 16px; cursor:pointer; background:#fff;
    transition:.12s border-color, .12s background;
    font-size:15px; line-height:1.4;
  }
  .opt:hover{border-color:var(--gold);}
  .opt.selected{border-color:var(--gold); background:#fdf6e8;}
  .opt input{margin-top:2px; accent-color:var(--gold);}
  .opt .lab{font-weight:700; color:var(--muted); width:18px;}

  .reveal{
    margin:18px 0 4px; padding:14px 16px; border-radius:4px;
    font-size:14px; line-height:1.5; display:none;
  }
  .reveal.show{display:block;}
  .reveal.correct{background:var(--green-soft); border:1px solid #b9dcc7; color:#1f5b3d;}
  .reveal.wrong{background:#fbe7e7; border:1px solid #ecbcbc; color:#7c2c2c;}

  .actionRow{
    display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:10px;
    padding:18px 30px 24px; border-top:1px solid var(--line);
    background:#fbfaf6;
  }
  button{
    font-family:inherit; font-size:13.5px; cursor:pointer;
    border-radius:3px; padding:10px 16px; border:1px solid var(--line);
    background:#fff; color:var(--ink); font-weight:600;
  }
  button:hover{border-color:var(--navy);}
  .btn-primary{background:var(--navy); color:#fff; border-color:var(--navy);}
  .btn-primary:hover{background:var(--navy-deep);}
  .btn-gold{background:var(--gold); border-color:var(--gold); color:#2a1d04;}
  .btn-gold:hover{background:#9c7126;}
  .btn-ghost{background:transparent;}
  .spacer{flex:1;}

  /* ---------- SIDE PANEL ---------- */
  .side{display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:16px;}
  .timerCard{
    background:var(--navy); color:#fff; border-radius:4px;
    padding:16px 18px; text-align:center;
  }
  .timerCard .lbl{font-size:11px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.1em; color:#b9c3d6;}
  .timerCard .val{font-family:'Courier New',monospace; font-size:26px; font-weight:700; margin-top:4px; color:var(--gold-soft);}

  .legend{
    background:var(--panel); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px;
    padding:14px 16px; font-size:12px;
  }
  .legend .row{display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px; margin-bottom:6px;}
  .legend .sw{width:14px;height:14px;border-radius:3px;flex-shrink:0;border:1px solid var(--line);}

  .navCard{
    background:var(--panel); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:14px 16px;
  }
  .navCard h4{margin:0 0 10px; font-size:12px; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted);}
  .navGrid{display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(8,1fr); gap:6px;}
  .navBtn{
    aspect-ratio:1; border-radius:3px; border:1px solid var(--line);
    background:#fff; font-size:12px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer;
    display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center; padding:0;
  }
  .navBtn.current{outline:2px solid var(--navy); outline-offset:1px;}
  .navBtn.answered{background:var(--green); color:#fff; border-color:var(--green);}
  .navBtn.marked{background:var(--violet); color:#fff; border-color:var(--violet);}
  .navBtn.answeredmarked{background:var(--gold); color:#2a1d04; border-color:var(--gold);}

  .subjJump{display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:6px; margin-top:12px;}
  .subjJump button{flex:1; font-size:11px; padding:7px 6px;}

  .statBox{
    background:var(--panel); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:14px 16px;
    font-size:13px;
  }
  .statBox .row{display:flex; justify-content:space-between; padding:4px 0; border-bottom:1px dashed var(--line);}
  .statBox .row:last-child{border-bottom:none;}

  /* ---------- START / RESULT SCREENS ---------- */
  .screen{
    max-width:760px; margin:50px auto; background:var(--panel);
    border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:42px 46px;
  }
  .screen h1{
    font-family:Georgia,'Times New Roman',serif; font-size:30px; margin:0 0 6px; color:var(--navy);
  }
  .screen p.sub{color:var(--muted); margin-top:0; font-size:14.5px;}
  .syllabusGrid{display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:14px; margin:28px 0;}
  .sylCard{border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:14px 16px;}
  .sylCard .n{font-family:Georgia,serif; font-size:26px; color:var(--gold); line-height:1;}
  .sylCard .t{font-size:13.5px; font-weight:700; margin:4px 0 2px;}
  .sylCard .d{font-size:12px; color:var(--muted);}

  .resultGrid{display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr); gap:14px; margin:24px 0;}
  .scoreCard{border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:16px;}
  .scoreCard .big{font-family:Georgia,serif; font-size:28px; color:var(--navy);}
  .scoreCard .lbl{font-size:11.5px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.06em; color:var(--muted); margin-top:4px;}
  .bar{height:8px;border-radius:4px;background:#ece8db;overflow:hidden; margin-top:8px;}
  .bar > div{height:100%; background:var(--green);}

  .reviewList{margin-top:30px;}
  .reviewItem{border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:4px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:10px;}
  .reviewItem .q{font-weight:600; margin-bottom:6px; font-size:14px;}
  .reviewItem .a{font-size:13px; margin:2px 0;}
  .reviewItem .ok{color:var(--green);}
  .reviewItem .bad{color:var(--red);}
  .hidden{display:none !important;}
  footer.note{text-align:center; color:var(--muted); font-size:11.5px; margin-top:30px;}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ============ START SCREEN ============ -->
<div class="screen" id="startScreen">
  <h1>CDAC CCEE Mock Test</h1>
  <p class="sub">PGCP-ESD &middot; Practice set covering RTOS, IoT, Embedded Device Drivers &amp; Aptitude &middot; 100 questions</p>
  <div class="syllabusGrid">
    <div class="sylCard"><div class="n">25</div><div class="t">Real-Time Operating Systems</div><div class="d">Scheduling, IPC, interrupts, priority inversion, FreeRTOS</div></div>
    <div class="sylCard"><div class="n">25</div><div class="t">Internet of Things</div><div class="d">Protocols, wireless standards, security, edge &amp; embedded AI</div></div>
    <div class="sylCard"><div class="n">25</div><div class="t">Embedded Device Drivers</div><div class="d">Linux kernel modules, char drivers, IOCTL, I2C/SPI, GPIO</div></div>
    <div class="sylCard"><div class="n">25</div><div class="t">Aptitude</div><div class="d">Quant, reasoning, series, blood relations, data sufficiency</div></div>
  </div>
  <label style="font-size:13px; display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; margin-bottom:18px;">
    <input type="checkbox" id="instantFeedback"> Show answer explanation immediately after each attempt (practice mode)
  </label>
  <button class="btn-gold" id="startBtn" style="width:100%; padding:14px; font-size:15px;">Begin Test</button>
  <footer class="note">Timer: 60 minutes &middot; Negative marking: none &middot; Free to fork on GitHub</footer>
</div>

<!-- ============ EXAM SCREEN ============ -->
<div id="examScreen" class="hidden">
  <div class="topbar">
    <div class="brand">
      <div class="mark">CC</div>
      <div class="title">CDAC CCEE Practice Portal<b id="candidateLine">Session #CCEE-2026</b></div>
    </div>
    <div class="meta">
      <div>Answered<b id="metaAnswered">0 / 100</b></div>
      <div>Marked<b id="metaMarked">0</b></div>
      <div>Unanswered<b id="metaUnanswered">100</b></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="stage">
    <div class="examGrid">
      <!-- question panel -->
      <div class="qpanel">
        <div class="qbar">
          <span class="tag" id="qTag">RTOS</span>
          <span class="qnum" id="qPos">Question 1 of 100</span>
        </div>
        <div class="qbody">
          <p class="qtext" id="qText">Loading…</p>
          <div class="options" id="qOptions"></div>
          <div class="reveal" id="qReveal"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="actionRow">
          <button class="btn-ghost" id="clearBtn">Clear Response</button>
          <button class="btn-ghost" id="markBtn">Mark for Review</button>
          <div class="spacer"></div>
          <button id="prevBtn">&larr; Previous</button>
          <button class="btn-primary" id="nextBtn">Save &amp; Next &rarr;</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- side panel -->
      <div class="side">
        <div class="timerCard">
          <div class="lbl">Time Remaining</div>
          <div class="val" id="timerVal">60:00</div>
        </div>

        <div class="legend">
          <div class="row"><span class="sw" style="background:var(--green);border-color:var(--green);"></span> Answered</div>
          <div class="row"><span class="sw" style="background:var(--violet);border-color:var(--violet);"></span> Marked for review</div>
          <div class="row"><span class="sw" style="background:var(--gold);border-color:var(--gold);"></span> Answered &amp; marked</div>
          <div class="row"><span class="sw" style="background:#fff;"></span> Not visited / unanswered</div>
        </div>

        <div class="navCard">
          <h4>Question Navigator</h4>
          <div class="navGrid" id="navGrid"></div>
          <div class="subjJump">
            <button data-jump="RTOS">RTOS</button>
            <button data-jump="IOT">IoT</button>
            <button data-jump="EDD">Drivers</button>
            <button data-jump="APT">Aptitude</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <button class="btn-primary" id="submitBtn" style="padding:13px;">Submit Test</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ============ RESULT SCREEN ============ -->
<div class="screen hidden" id="resultScreen" style="max-width:900px;">
  <h1>Your Results</h1>
  <p class="sub">Here's how the attempt broke down across all four subjects.</p>
  <div class="resultGrid" id="resultGrid"></div>
  <div class="resultGrid" id="subjectGrid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);"></div>
  <div style="margin:20px 0; display:flex; gap:10px;">
    <button class="btn-primary" id="reviewBtn">Review All Answers</button>
    <button class="btn-gold" id="retakeBtn">Retake Test</button>
  </div>
  <div class="reviewList hidden" id="reviewList"></div>
</div>

<script>
/* ===================== QUESTION BANK ===================== */
const Q = [];

/* ---------- RTOS (25) ---------- */
const rtos = [
["Which best defines a hard real-time system?",["Missing a deadline causes system failure","Deadlines are flexible","No deadlines exist","Deadlines only affect performance"],0,
 "In hard real-time systems, a missed deadline is treated as a system failure, unlike soft real-time systems where it merely degrades quality."],
["Which of these is NOT a typical task state in an RTOS?",["Running","Ready","Blocked","Compiled"],3,
 "Compiled is a build-time concept, not a runtime task state. RTOS tasks move between Running, Ready, Blocked/Suspended."],
["Context switching refers to:",["Switching power modes","Saving and restoring CPU state between tasks","Switching network protocols","Compiling context-free grammars"],1,
 "A context switch saves the registers/stack pointer of the outgoing task and restores them for the incoming task."],
["In preemptive scheduling, a higher priority task:",["Waits for the running task to finish","Can interrupt and take over the CPU","Is always run last","Cannot run until reset"],1,
 "Preemptive schedulers immediately switch to a higher priority task that becomes ready, interrupting the current one."],
["Rate Monotonic (RM) scheduling assigns task priority based on:",["Task arrival time","Task period — shorter period gets higher priority","Random assignment","Memory usage"],1,
 "RM is a fixed-priority scheme where tasks with shorter periods are assigned higher priority."],
["Earliest Deadline First (EDF) is an example of:",["Static priority scheduling","Dynamic priority scheduling","FIFO scheduling","Round robin only"],1,
 "EDF recalculates priority dynamically — the task with the nearest absolute deadline always runs next."],
["Priority inversion occurs when:",["A high priority task is blocked by a lower priority task holding a needed resource","Tasks have equal priority","ISR priority is higher than tasks","Round robin scheduling is used"],0,
 "Classic priority inversion: a high priority task waits on a mutex held by a low priority task, effectively inverting their priorities."],
["The priority ceiling protocol primarily helps prevent:",["Stack overflow","Unbounded priority inversion","Memory leaks","Deadline misses in soft RTOS only"],1,
 "Priority ceiling bounds the blocking time a high-priority task can experience, preventing unbounded inversion."],
["A mutex differs from a binary semaphore mainly because a mutex:",["Supports priority inheritance and has ownership semantics","Can only be binary","Can be used freely inside an ISR","Has no real difference"],0,
 "Mutexes are owned by the locking task and typically support priority inheritance; semaphores have no ownership concept."],
["Message queues in an RTOS are primarily used for:",["Inter-task communication","Memory protection","Compiling tasks","Power management"],0,
 "Queues let tasks (and ISRs) pass data items between each other safely."],
["Stack overflow detection in an RTOS is typically implemented by:",["Checking watermark/canary values at stack boundaries","Disabling interrupts","Increasing CPU clock","Ignoring it — RTOS handles it automatically"],0,
 "A canary/watermark pattern written at the end of a task's stack is checked periodically or on context switch to detect overflow."],
["The RTOS tick is generated by:",["A periodic hardware timer interrupt","A software polling loop only","The idle task","The compiler"],0,
 "A hardware timer fires at a fixed interval to drive the scheduler's time base (the 'tick')."],
["Tickless idle mode is used primarily to:",["Increase CPU clock speed","Reduce power consumption when no task needs to run","Improve graphics rendering","Disable all interrupts permanently"],1,
 "Tickless idle suppresses the periodic tick interrupt during idle periods so the MCU can sleep longer and save power."],
["Code running inside an ISR should generally:",["Perform long computations","Be kept as short as possible, deferring heavy work to a task","Always call blocking RTOS functions","Never be used in RTOS systems"],1,
 "ISRs should do minimal work and hand off processing to a deferred task to keep interrupt latency low."],
["Deferred interrupt handling typically relies on:",["A deferred procedure / task notification mechanism","Increasing interrupt priority","Disabling the interrupt forever","Polling only"],0,
 "The ISR signals a task (e.g. via semaphore/notification) which then performs the heavier processing outside interrupt context."],
["A watchdog timer in an embedded RTOS system is used to:",["Reset the system if a task fails to refresh it in time","Increase scheduling speed","Manage memory allocation","Encrypt data"],0,
 "If the watchdog isn't periodically 'kicked' by healthy software, it resets the system — a safety net against hangs."],
["Worst-Case Execution Time (WCET) is important because it:",["Helps determine if deadlines can be met","Is used only for memory sizing","Has no role in scheduling analysis","Only applies to soft real-time systems"],0,
 "Schedulability analyses (RM, EDF, response-time analysis) all rely on a reliable WCET estimate per task."],
["A critical section in RTOS programming is:",["A code region needing exclusive access to a shared resource","The fastest part of the code","A section that always runs in an ISR","Unrelated to synchronization"],0,
 "Critical sections protect shared data from concurrent access using locks, disabling interrupts, or scheduler locks."],
["Which condition is NOT required for a deadlock to occur?",["Mutual exclusion","Hold and wait","Preemption allowed","Circular wait"],2,
 "The four classic deadlock conditions are mutual exclusion, hold-and-wait, NO preemption, and circular wait."],
["For Rate Monotonic scheduling, as the number of tasks n increases, the utilization bound approaches approximately:",["100%","ln(2) ≈ 69.3%","50%","0%"],1,
 "Liu & Layland's bound n(2^(1/n)-1) converges to ln(2) ≈ 0.693 as n → ∞."],
["In FreeRTOS, calling vTaskDelay() places the calling task into which state?",["Running","Blocked (delayed)","Suspended permanently","Ready only"],1,
 "vTaskDelay() blocks the task for the specified number of ticks, allowing other tasks to run."],
["Static task allocation (vs dynamic) in an RTOS mainly improves:",["Predictability and avoids heap fragmentation","Code readability only","Network throughput","GPU performance"],0,
 "Pre-allocating task stacks/TCBs at compile time avoids runtime heap fragmentation and gives deterministic memory behaviour."],
["In mixed-criticality systems, the primary design goal is to:",["Run all tasks at the same priority","Isolate tasks of different criticality so low-criticality faults don't affect high-criticality tasks","Remove the scheduler entirely","Disable interrupts globally"],1,
 "Mixed-criticality design partitions resources/time so a failure in a non-critical task cannot compromise safety-critical functions."],
["Response Time Analysis is used to:",["Verify each task meets its deadline under worst-case interference","Measure power consumption","Test network latency only","Compile code faster"],0,
 "RTA computes a task's worst-case response time accounting for blocking and preemption from higher-priority tasks."],
["A semaphore used purely for signaling between an ISR and a task is typically:",["A binary semaphore","A file descriptor","A device tree node","A kernel module"],0,
 "A binary semaphore (give/take) is the lightweight, ISR-safe primitive commonly used for ISR-to-task signaling."]
];

/* ---------- IoT (25) ---------- */
const iot = [
["Which layer of the IoT architecture is responsible for sensing physical parameters?",["Application layer","Perception layer","Network layer","Middleware layer"],1,
 "The perception (or sensing) layer contains sensors/actuators that gather raw physical data."],
["MQTT QoS level 0 means:",["At least once delivery","Exactly once delivery","At most once delivery (fire and forget)","Guaranteed delivery with acknowledgment"],2,
 "QoS 0 sends the message once with no acknowledgment or retry — it may be lost."],
["Compared to MQTT, CoAP is primarily designed for:",["TCP-based publish/subscribe only","Constrained devices over UDP using a REST-like model","Only HTTPS communication","Replacing IPv6"],1,
 "CoAP runs over UDP and mirrors REST methods (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE), suited to very constrained nodes."],
["Zigbee (IEEE 802.15.4) commonly operates in which frequency band?",["2.4 GHz","5 GHz","60 GHz","433 MHz only"],0,
 "Zigbee most commonly uses the globally available 2.4 GHz ISM band (also supports 868/915 MHz regionally)."],
["Compared to Bluetooth Classic, BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy) is designed for:",["Higher data rate streaming","Low power, intermittent small data transfers","Long range cellular communication","Wired communication"],1,
 "BLE trades throughput for very low power consumption, ideal for periodic small payloads like sensor readings."],
["LoRaWAN is best characterized as a:",["Low Power Wide Area Network technology","Short range NFC protocol","High bandwidth fiber protocol","Wired industrial bus"],0,
 "LoRaWAN provides long-range, low-power communication for IoT devices, trading off data rate for range and battery life."],
["6LoWPAN enables:",["IPv6 communication over low power wireless networks like 802.15.4","Only IPv4 routing","Bluetooth pairing","MQTT broker discovery"],0,
 "6LoWPAN compresses/adapts IPv6 packets so they can run efficiently over low-power, low-bandwidth links such as 802.15.4."],
["REST architecture is based on which core principle?",["Stateful sessions only","Stateless client-server communication using standard methods","Binary-only payloads","Mandatory use of an MQTT broker"],1,
 "REST relies on stateless requests using uniform methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) over resources identified by URIs."],
["IEEE 802.15.4 primarily defines the standard for:",["Wireless LAN (WiFi)","Low-rate wireless personal area networks (LR-WPAN)","Cellular 5G","Fiber optic communication"],1,
 "802.15.4 is the PHY/MAC standard underlying Zigbee and other low-rate WPAN technologies."],
["IEEE 802.11 standards primarily define:",["Wireless LAN (WiFi)","Bluetooth","Zigbee","LoRa"],0,
 "802.11 is the family of standards that defines WiFi."],
["NB-IoT (Narrowband IoT) is designed mainly for:",["High-speed video streaming","Low power, wide area cellular connectivity for IoT devices","Local Bluetooth mesh","Wired Ethernet replacement"],1,
 "NB-IoT is a cellular LPWAN technology optimized for deep coverage, long battery life, and small periodic data."],
["Edge computing primarily aims to:",["Move all processing to a centralized cloud only","Process data closer to the source to reduce latency","Eliminate the need for sensors","Replace networking entirely"],1,
 "Edge computing pushes computation near the data source, cutting round-trip latency and bandwidth use."],
["In MQTT, the broker's main role is to:",["Generate sensor data","Manage publish-subscribe message routing between clients","Encrypt all traffic by default","Replace the need for topics"],1,
 "The broker receives published messages and routes them to subscribers of the matching topic."],
["Secure boot in embedded/IoT security ensures that:",["The device boots faster only","The device only runs verified/trusted firmware at startup","The device runs any firmware","All security checks are disabled for speed"],1,
 "Secure boot cryptographically verifies firmware signatures before execution, preventing unauthorized code from running."],
["TLS/DTLS are used in IoT primarily to provide:",["Faster data transfer with no encryption","Secure, encrypted communication channels","Power saving","Device pairing only"],1,
 "TLS (over TCP) and DTLS (over UDP) provide authenticated, encrypted channels for IoT communication."],
["TensorFlow Lite Micro is designed to run ML models on:",["Large cloud servers only","Resource-constrained microcontrollers","Desktop GPUs exclusively","Mainframe computers"],1,
 "TFLite Micro is built for inference on MCUs with very limited memory and no OS, enabling embedded AI."],
["OTA (Over-The-Air) updates in IoT allow:",["Remote firmware updates without physical access","Only hardware replacement","Manual reflashing via JTAG only","Permanently disabling the device"],0,
 "OTA/FOTA lets devices receive new firmware images over the network, avoiding manual field servicing."],
["Device provisioning in IoT refers to:",["Manufacturing the device's PCB","Configuring and registering a device for first use on a network/platform","Discarding old devices","Encrypting cloud storage only"],1,
 "Provisioning sets identity, credentials, and configuration so a device can securely join a network/platform."],
